Methodology. The estimate is grounded in actual 2025 IB review activity: 186 work papers completed across 6 reviews using 71 reviewer-assignments, with each review comprising a two-week fieldwork period — an observed effort of approximately 30.5 hours per work paper. As a reasonableness check, this 2025 rate was compared against a long-run normalized average of approximately 27 hours per work paper drawn from 2024–2026 data; the two are consistent, confirming that 2025 is a representative base year rather than an outlier. Because the 2027 book of work is not yet planned, 2025 serves as the most recent representative year for grounding the estimate in observed production. All savings figures below are computed on the 2025 basis.


